00:00:09.911 --> 00:00:11.880 position:30% line:83% align:start
[ANNOUNCER 1A]
It's the second and last day

00:00:12.012 --> 00:00:13.413 position:27% line:83% align:start
of the Patissier
World Tournament,

00:00:13.548 --> 00:00:15.984 position:16% line:83% align:start
and we've at last arrived
at the grand finale!

00:00:16.116 --> 00:00:18.920 position:27% line:89% align:start
[excited chatter]

00:00:19.052 --> 00:00:20.555 position:24% line:83% align:start
[MALE REPORTER 1A]
Pure spectacle.

00:00:20.688 --> 00:00:23.825 position:5% line:83% align:start
It's no wonder why they call him
the Patissier Chosen One.

00:00:23.958 --> 00:00:25.459 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's magnificent!

00:00:26.093 --> 00:00:26.895 position:21% line:83% align:start
[FEMALE REPORTER 1A]
The challenge

00:00:27.027 --> 00:00:27.829 position:24% line:89% align:start
for the final round

00:00:27.962 --> 00:00:29.363 position:24% line:89% align:start
is candy sculpture.

00:00:29.496 --> 00:00:30.832 position:19% line:89% align:start
He's almost guaranteed

00:00:30.965 --> 00:00:33.066 position:35% line:83% align:start
to be named
the world's greatest Patissier!

00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:34.802 position:27% line:89% align:start
[breathes deeply]

00:00:43.443 --> 00:00:45.112 position:35% line:83% align:start
[PATISSIER]
Just look around.

00:00:45.245 --> 00:00:47.447 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's a wonderland of sweets.

00:00:48.482 --> 00:00:50.117 position:19% line:89% align:start
I will win this thing.

00:00:50.484 --> 00:00:52.587 position:44% line:83% align:start
Then,
I'll finally have achieved it,

00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:54.556 position:24% line:89% align:start
my childhood dream!

00:00:55.623 --> 00:00:57.357 position:16% line:83% align:start
[ANNOUNCER 1A] The chefs
are moving their finished pieces

00:00:57.491 --> 00:00:59.226 position:16% line:89% align:start
to the judging area now.

00:01:01.763 --> 00:01:03.598 position:21% line:89% align:start
This is it. On three.

00:01:03.731 --> 00:01:05.265 position:24% line:89% align:start
One, two... three!

00:01:06.801 --> 00:01:09.037 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:01:09.169 --> 00:01:12.439 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:01:12.574 --> 00:01:13.473 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:01:18.245 --> 00:01:23.017 position:24% line:89% align:start
[panicked chatter]

00:01:23.150 --> 00:01:24.686 position:35% line:83% align:start
[PATISSIER]
This feeling...

00:01:24.819 --> 00:01:27.087 position:27% line:89% align:start
Huh, am I dying?

00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:28.756 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Patissier sighs]

00:01:28.890 --> 00:01:31.224 position:10% line:83% align:start
[PATISSIER] I wanted to make
the world's greatest sweets

00:01:31.358 --> 00:01:32.827 position:21% line:89% align:start
before I passed away.

00:01:33.795 --> 00:01:35.763 position:21% line:83% align:start
I was going to create
a land of sweets

00:01:35.897 --> 00:01:38.533 position:10% line:83% align:start
that made everyone everywhere
smile.

00:01:38.900 --> 00:01:40.835 position:19% line:89% align:start
That dream is over now.

00:01:42.070 --> 00:01:45.172 position:13% line:89% align:start
God, you are far too cruel.

00:01:45.305 --> 00:01:48.042 position:44% line:83% align:start
[GOD]
Well, then, so be it.

00:01:48.175 --> 00:01:50.511 position:27% line:83% align:start
I shall grant you
one more chance.

00:01:50.645 --> 00:01:53.146 position:35% line:83% align:start
[PATISSIER]
Huh? Who's there?

00:01:54.281 --> 00:01:57.150 position:44% line:83% align:start
[GOD]
Your new name shall be

00:01:57.284 --> 00:01:59.721 position:21% line:89% align:start
Pastry Mille Morteln!

00:03:41.823 --> 00:03:43.256 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
The Fief of Morteln.

00:03:43.390 --> 00:03:45.760 position:35% line:83% align:start
My father,
Casserole Mille Morteln,

00:03:45.893 --> 00:03:48.261 position:21% line:83% align:start
is the suzerain lord
of this place.

00:03:48.395 --> 00:03:50.430 position:35% line:83% align:start
Before him,
it was a barren land.

00:03:50.565 --> 00:03:52.033 position:21% line:83% align:start
One that could barely
grow wheat.

00:03:52.166 --> 00:03:53.034 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:03:54.401 --> 00:03:55.903 position:7% line:83% align:start
-[HANDLER 1A] Easy there, boy.
-[PAS] My father worked hard

00:03:56.037 --> 00:03:58.271 position:30% line:83% align:start
alongside those
who moved there with him

00:03:58.405 --> 00:04:00.208 position:30% line:83% align:start
and the people
already living there.

00:04:00.340 --> 00:04:02.510 position:38% line:83% align:start
Together,
they spent almost 20 years

00:04:02.643 --> 00:04:04.946 position:5% line:89% align:start
diligently cultivating the soil.

00:04:06.080 --> 00:04:07.815 position:16% line:89% align:start
That hard work paid off.

00:04:07.949 --> 00:04:11.152 position:21% line:83% align:start
We've managed to grow
to a fief of three villages.

00:04:11.318 --> 00:04:12.720 position:10% line:89% align:start
They're about 40 people each

00:04:12.854 --> 00:04:15.790 position:33% line:83% align:start
with harvests
of both wheat and barley.

00:04:16.624 --> 00:04:18.325 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Come now! Give it your all!

00:04:18.458 --> 00:04:19.727 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
I'm just getting warmed up!

00:04:19.861 --> 00:04:24.132 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[metal clanging]
-[grunting]

00:04:24.264 --> 00:04:27.702 position:38% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:04:27.835 --> 00:04:30.403 position:21% line:83% align:start
You're getting sloppy
with your grip again.

00:04:30.538 --> 00:04:31.706 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Yes, sir.

00:04:34.542 --> 00:04:36.778 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's been nine years
since I was reincarnated

00:04:36.911 --> 00:04:39.446 position:10% line:83% align:start
as the son of suzerain lord,
Sir Casserole.

00:04:39.580 --> 00:04:40.681 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Pas grunting]

00:04:40.815 --> 00:04:42.349 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
That's it!

00:04:42.482 --> 00:04:44.218 position:30% line:83% align:start
Grip so firmly
I'd have to tear off your hand

00:04:44.384 --> 00:04:45.418 position:24% line:89% align:start
to get that blade.

00:04:45.553 --> 00:04:48.790 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yes, sir! [grunting]

00:04:48.923 --> 00:04:52.560 position:5% line:83% align:start
[PAS] I was raised by my father,
a military hero,

00:04:52.693 --> 00:04:56.130 position:30% line:83% align:start
my kind mother
and my five older sisters.

00:04:56.264 --> 00:04:57.932 position:38% line:83% align:start
It's been
a relatively happy life.

00:04:58.065 --> 00:05:01.401 position:41% line:83% align:start
Except,
our fief can't grow sugar.

00:05:01.869 --> 00:05:03.370 position:35% line:83% align:start
That means
it's nearly impossible

00:05:03.504 --> 00:05:05.139 position:16% line:89% align:start
to get sweet things here.

00:05:05.273 --> 00:05:08.408 position:13% line:83% align:start
Gosh, how nice it would be
to make sweets again!

00:05:08.543 --> 00:05:09.877 position:7% line:83% align:start
-[CASSEROLE] You're distracted!
-[Pas gasps]

00:05:11.813 --> 00:05:12.713 position:41% line:89% align:start
[thuds]

00:05:13.648 --> 00:05:14.682 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Pas groaning]

00:05:14.816 --> 00:05:17.251 position:13% line:89% align:start
My lord! I have some news!

00:05:17.417 --> 00:05:18.753 position:24% line:89% align:start
Still at it, I see.

00:05:19.220 --> 00:05:22.290 position:16% line:83% align:start
I doubt you're even aware
it's almost time for breakfast.

00:05:22.422 --> 00:05:24.559 position:41% line:83% align:start
Right,
then we'll end our lesson here.

00:05:24.692 --> 00:05:29.163 position:21% line:83% align:start
[gasping] Yes, sir.
Thank you very much.

00:05:29.297 --> 00:05:30.865 position:16% line:89% align:start
Now then, Feuille. Go on.

00:05:30.998 --> 00:05:33.568 position:21% line:83% align:start
I have both good news
and bad news for you.

00:05:33.701 --> 00:05:35.002 position:16% line:89% align:start
Which do you want first?

00:05:35.136 --> 00:05:37.138 position:35% line:83% align:start
Regardless,
I'll have to listen to them each

00:05:37.271 --> 00:05:38.471 position:30% line:89% align:start
in due course.

00:05:38.606 --> 00:05:40.141 position:38% line:83% align:start
I suppose
let's start with the good.

00:05:40.274 --> 00:05:43.410 position:5% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE] Right. The bean fields
are absolutely thriving.

00:05:43.544 --> 00:05:45.445 position:27% line:83% align:start
They should yield
a significant harvest.

00:05:45.913 --> 00:05:48.115 position:13% line:83% align:start
Seems like the kid's advice
worked out.

00:05:48.749 --> 00:05:50.551 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Sprinkle lime on the soil.

00:05:50.685 --> 00:05:52.320 position:27% line:83% align:start
That will improve
the crop yield!

00:05:52.452 --> 00:05:53.321 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
It appears I was right

00:05:53.453 --> 00:05:55.022 position:16% line:89% align:start
to take your suggestion.

00:05:55.857 --> 00:05:57.859 position:10% line:83% align:start
We'll have a bumper bean crop
this year.

00:05:57.992 --> 00:06:00.628 position:19% line:83% align:start
I may still be limited
to simple bean dishes at first,

00:06:00.761 --> 00:06:03.598 position:5% line:83% align:start
but caramelized roasted soybeans
are a classic tea snack.

00:06:03.731 --> 00:06:06.534 position:24% line:83% align:start
You can sprinkle on
soybean flour for extra flavor.

00:06:06.667 --> 00:06:08.870 position:19% line:83% align:start
Wherever did you learn
about such things?

00:06:09.003 --> 00:06:10.137 position:35% line:89% align:start
[yelps] Oh!

00:06:10.271 --> 00:06:11.939 position:13% line:83% align:start
[PAS] They wouldn't believe
it's because...

00:06:12.073 --> 00:06:13.074 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Just more daydreams.
-[PAS] ...I was reincarnated.

00:06:13.541 --> 00:06:15.475 position:19% line:89% align:start
Well, strange as it is,

00:06:15.610 --> 00:06:18.112 position:16% line:83% align:start
you've always been prone
to such flights of fancy.

00:06:18.246 --> 00:06:21.515 position:7% line:83% align:start
That imagination of yours has
produced a lot of great ideas,

00:06:21.649 --> 00:06:23.684 position:16% line:83% align:start
and they've all resulted
in good things for the fief

00:06:23.818 --> 00:06:25.452 position:16% line:89% align:start
over the past few years.

00:06:25.586 --> 00:06:27.989 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's like you're already
a little shadow suzerain!

00:06:28.122 --> 00:06:29.257 position:30% line:89% align:start
[clears throat]

00:06:29.389 --> 00:06:32.159 position:5% line:83% align:start
Now, it's time for the bad news,
Feuille.

00:06:32.293 --> 00:06:33.194 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:06:33.828 --> 00:06:35.162 position:7% line:89% align:start
Regarding the County of Retes,

00:06:35.296 --> 00:06:37.932 position:27% line:83% align:start
attempts to stop
some bandits there have failed.

00:06:38.332 --> 00:06:40.433 position:5% line:89% align:start
[grunts] The bandits prevailed?

00:06:40.568 --> 00:06:42.103 position:38% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE]
I'm told the stragglers escaped,

00:06:42.236 --> 00:06:43.337 position:16% line:89% align:start
and are heading our way.

00:06:43.470 --> 00:06:44.305 position:38% line:89% align:start
How many?

00:06:44.437 --> 00:06:45.840 position:27% line:89% align:start
There's about 50.

00:06:46.774 --> 00:06:50.344 position:13% line:83% align:start
[PAS] If bandits come here,
they'll ravage our fields.

00:06:50.477 --> 00:06:52.346 position:30% line:83% align:start
Both the beans
we worked so hard for

00:06:52.479 --> 00:06:54.081 position:19% line:89% align:start
and our precious wheat.

00:06:54.649 --> 00:06:55.883 position:38% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE]
At their current pace,

00:06:56.017 --> 00:06:57.985 position:24% line:83% align:start
they should arrive
in two months' time.

00:06:58.119 --> 00:06:59.520 position:27% line:89% align:start
Only two months.

00:06:59.654 --> 00:07:02.056 position:30% line:83% align:start
Our only chance
is to rally the villagers.

00:07:02.189 --> 00:07:03.456 position:21% line:89% align:start
We must try our best

00:07:03.591 --> 00:07:05.226 position:27% line:83% align:start
to drive them off
with pikes and slings.

00:07:05.626 --> 00:07:08.229 position:21% line:83% align:start
[PAS] Even if we pull
from all three villages,

00:07:08.362 --> 00:07:10.531 position:13% line:89% align:start
that's only 30 men at most.

00:07:10.665 --> 00:07:12.800 position:21% line:83% align:start
We'll barely be able
to slow them down.

00:07:12.934 --> 00:07:14.635 position:13% line:89% align:start
And in a prolonged battle,

00:07:14.769 --> 00:07:16.137 position:19% line:89% align:start
we're doomed for sure.

00:07:16.270 --> 00:07:17.939 position:5% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE] Perhaps we could use
the village canal

00:07:18.072 --> 00:07:19.307 position:27% line:89% align:start
to our advantage.

00:07:19.439 --> 00:07:20.775 position:16% line:89% align:start
Hole up there to buy time

00:07:20.908 --> 00:07:23.377 position:19% line:83% align:start
while I ask Count Retes
for reinforcements.

00:07:23.744 --> 00:07:25.579 position:5% line:89% align:start
If anyone could do it, it's you.

00:07:25.713 --> 00:07:27.081 position:27% line:89% align:start
Just one problem.

00:07:27.782 --> 00:07:30.651 position:33% line:83% align:start
That would be
Count Retes's reputation.

00:07:30.785 --> 00:07:32.119 position:5% line:89% align:start
If we were to defeat the bandits

00:07:32.253 --> 00:07:33.988 position:19% line:83% align:start
that the county failed
to stamp out,

00:07:34.121 --> 00:07:37.291 position:13% line:83% align:start
it would subject the count
to accusations of incompetence.

00:07:38.192 --> 00:07:42.196 position:21% line:83% align:start
That means we cannot
rely on them for reinforcements.

00:07:42.330 --> 00:07:44.098 position:38% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE]
The ideal outcome for the count

00:07:44.231 --> 00:07:45.465 position:19% line:89% align:start
would be for us to fail

00:07:45.599 --> 00:07:46.934 position:41% line:83% align:start
so that
the Margravate of Hubarek...

00:07:47.068 --> 00:07:49.003 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
What will become of Father?

00:07:49.136 --> 00:07:52.640 position:7% line:83% align:start
He has three resident retainers
including Feuille.

00:07:52.773 --> 00:07:54.408 position:13% line:89% align:start
It won't be an easy fight.

00:07:55.276 --> 00:07:57.945 position:33% line:83% align:start
But the beans
and most of all the wheat,

00:07:58.079 --> 00:08:00.581 position:30% line:83% align:start
I need them all
for making sweets!

00:08:00.715 --> 00:08:03.017 position:10% line:89% align:start
They can't take that from me.

00:08:03.150 --> 00:08:04.051 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:08:06.420 --> 00:08:07.755 position:38% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE]
I like that look, kid.

00:08:07.888 --> 00:08:09.690 position:21% line:83% align:start
He's finally starting
to feel his calling

00:08:09.824 --> 00:08:12.159 position:33% line:83% align:start
as our fief's
next suzerain lord.

00:08:13.894 --> 00:08:15.663 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
I won't lose it again.

00:08:15.796 --> 00:08:19.000 position:27% line:83% align:start
My precious dream
to create a land of sweets.

00:08:19.133 --> 00:08:21.969 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'll make them regret
the day they were born!

00:08:22.370 --> 00:08:23.671 position:13% line:89% align:start
No matter how you slice it,

00:08:23.804 --> 00:08:25.072 position:27% line:83% align:start
the only way out
of this situation

00:08:25.206 --> 00:08:27.008 position:10% line:83% align:start
is going to be a big gamble,
friend.

00:08:27.141 --> 00:08:29.744 position:30% line:83% align:start
Mind that this
is just my instinct talking.

00:08:29.877 --> 00:08:31.379 position:30% line:89% align:start
I have an idea.

00:08:31.512 --> 00:08:33.948 position:13% line:83% align:start
What if we use the kid here
as our secret trump card?

00:08:34.081 --> 00:08:34.749 position:41% line:89% align:start
How so?

00:08:34.882 --> 00:08:36.317 position:19% line:89% align:start
If the gamble pays off,

00:08:36.450 --> 00:08:38.986 position:21% line:83% align:start
your son may live up
to your reputation after all.

00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:41.689 position:10% line:83% align:start
You know I've always trusted
your instinct,

00:08:41.822 --> 00:08:43.824 position:10% line:89% align:start
but it would take magic to...

00:08:44.291 --> 00:08:45.159 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:08:45.626 --> 00:08:46.761 position:24% line:89% align:start
The Sanctification!

00:08:46.894 --> 00:08:48.295 position:38% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE]
Exactly!

00:08:48.429 --> 00:08:49.530 position:47% line:89% align:start
Uh?

00:08:50.731 --> 00:08:53.134 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Agnes, Josephine, listen to me.

00:08:54.001 --> 00:08:56.037 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm going to put Pas through
the Sanctification Ceremony.

00:08:56.170 --> 00:08:57.905 position:41% line:83% align:start
[AGNES]
[gasps] Darling, no!

00:08:58.039 --> 00:09:01.075 position:7% line:83% align:start
Surely that is asking too much
too soon of our sweet boy.

00:09:01.208 --> 00:09:02.676 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
You know as well as I do

00:09:02.810 --> 00:09:04.345 position:19% line:89% align:start
how bright our son is.

00:09:04.478 --> 00:09:06.814 position:5% line:83% align:start
He's at the top of his age group
in many things,

00:09:06.947 --> 00:09:08.182 position:21% line:89% align:start
including the sword.

00:09:08.315 --> 00:09:09.283 position:33% line:89% align:start
But still...

00:09:09.417 --> 00:09:10.951 position:10% line:89% align:start
I've made my decision, Agnes.

00:09:11.085 --> 00:09:13.587 position:24% line:83% align:start
He is accomplished
with both pen and blade.

00:09:14.021 --> 00:09:15.589 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
The Sanctification Ceremony

00:09:15.723 --> 00:09:18.092 position:30% line:83% align:start
is this world's
coming-of-age ritual.

00:09:18.225 --> 00:09:19.260 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm only nine,

00:09:19.393 --> 00:09:20.828 position:21% line:83% align:start
so it is a bit early
for me to take it,

00:09:20.961 --> 00:09:22.463 position:19% line:89% align:start
but that's what I want!

00:09:23.197 --> 00:09:26.667 position:16% line:83% align:start
[PAS] Still, this must be
a real shock for Mother.

00:09:26.801 --> 00:09:28.869 position:19% line:83% align:start
[PAS] Kids are usually
between 13 and 15

00:09:29.003 --> 00:09:30.271 position:19% line:89% align:start
when they participate.

00:09:30.404 --> 00:09:32.873 position:24% line:83% align:start
Though, I had hoped
for just a little longer

00:09:33.007 --> 00:09:35.009 position:7% line:89% align:start
with our sweet boy as a child.

00:09:35.142 --> 00:09:37.178 position:5% line:89% align:start
We set out in three days' time.

00:09:37.311 --> 00:09:38.679 position:19% line:89% align:start
Make the preparations.

00:09:38.813 --> 00:09:39.713 position:41% line:83% align:start
[AGNES]
I will.

00:09:40.347 --> 00:09:42.616 position:16% line:83% align:start
Josie, how would you like
to help me with that?

00:09:42.750 --> 00:09:45.019 position:5% line:83% align:start
-Certainly, Mother! I'd love to!
-After all,

00:09:45.152 --> 00:09:48.422 position:7% line:83% align:start
our little Pas must represent
the entire family's reputation

00:09:48.557 --> 00:09:49.757 position:19% line:89% align:start
before becoming a man.

00:09:49.890 --> 00:09:52.093 position:30% line:83% align:start
That's correct.
He must be perfect. Yes.

00:09:52.226 --> 00:09:54.161 position:10% line:83% align:start
-[Agnes, Josephine giggling]
-[PAS] Not good.

00:09:54.295 --> 00:09:56.363 position:24% line:83% align:start
It never bodes well
when they smile like that!

00:09:56.497 --> 00:09:57.598 position:19% line:89% align:start
Please help me, Father!

00:09:57.731 --> 00:09:59.433 position:19% line:89% align:start
Sorry eating. [slurps]

00:09:59.568 --> 00:10:01.802 position:27% line:89% align:start
[crying] Father!

00:10:01.936 --> 00:10:04.672 position:24% line:83% align:start
[AGNES, JOSEPHINE]
So cute!

00:10:04.805 --> 00:10:06.173 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Wait a minute!

00:10:06.307 --> 00:10:08.642 position:24% line:83% align:start
How do you not see
that you're traumatizing me?

00:10:08.776 --> 00:10:10.878 position:24% line:83% align:start
Aw, doesn't he look
so precious like that!

00:10:11.011 --> 00:10:13.447 position:19% line:83% align:start
Now all that's missing
is the perfect pair of shoes!

00:10:13.582 --> 00:10:15.015 position:16% line:89% align:start
But Josie, am I mistaken,

00:10:15.149 --> 00:10:17.017 position:7% line:83% align:start
-or is that your favorite pair?
-It's no big deal!

00:10:17.151 --> 00:10:19.320 position:33% line:83% align:start
Only the best
for my sweet little brother!

00:10:19.887 --> 00:10:22.123 position:41% line:83% align:start
Great!
Now it's time to do his makeup!

00:10:22.256 --> 00:10:24.725 position:38% line:83% align:start
Your skin
is the ideal blank canvas!

00:10:24.859 --> 00:10:26.760 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Resistance is futile.

00:10:26.894 --> 00:10:28.129 position:16% line:89% align:start
Ever since I was little,

00:10:28.262 --> 00:10:29.763 position:21% line:83% align:start
my mother and sisters
have treated me

00:10:29.897 --> 00:10:32.366 position:30% line:83% align:start
like some kind
of real-life dress-up doll.

00:10:33.535 --> 00:10:35.903 position:33% line:83% align:start
Back when all
of my older sisters were around,

00:10:36.036 --> 00:10:38.305 position:19% line:89% align:start
it was far, far worse!

00:10:38.873 --> 00:10:40.674 position:24% line:83% align:start
You look just like
the belle of the ball,

00:10:40.808 --> 00:10:42.977 position:33% line:83% align:start
-little bro!
-[PAS] Father!

00:10:43.110 --> 00:10:44.778 position:19% line:89% align:start
I need to be an adult.

00:10:44.912 --> 00:10:47.181 position:19% line:89% align:start
The situation is dire!

00:10:49.884 --> 00:10:51.620 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
What's the matter, my son?

00:10:51.785 --> 00:10:53.287 position:21% line:89% align:start
How are you exhausted

00:10:53.420 --> 00:10:55.389 position:10% line:83% align:start
when today is just the outset
of our long journey ahead?

00:10:55.524 --> 00:10:57.958 position:30% line:83% align:start
Well, it's been
a rather hectic three days,

00:10:58.092 --> 00:10:58.993 position:38% line:89% align:start
you know?

00:11:00.361 --> 00:11:01.929 position:33% line:89% align:start
Sweet Pas...

00:11:03.632 --> 00:11:04.698 position:24% line:89% align:start
be safe out there.

00:11:04.832 --> 00:11:06.700 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Give it your best!
-Right!

00:11:06.834 --> 00:11:08.702 position:33% line:89% align:start
Oi! Hey, Pas!

00:11:08.836 --> 00:11:11.272 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's Marc and Lumi and the guys!

00:11:11.405 --> 00:11:12.339 position:30% line:89% align:start
How 'bout that?

00:11:12.473 --> 00:11:13.974 position:24% line:89% align:start
Such a lucky duck!

00:11:14.108 --> 00:11:16.477 position:16% line:83% align:start
I wanna go to the capital
dressed up in a fancy suit!

00:11:16.611 --> 00:11:17.745 position:38% line:89% align:start
Bad idea.

00:11:17.878 --> 00:11:19.380 position:5% line:83% align:start
-You would look awful in a suit.
-Hm?

00:11:19.514 --> 00:11:21.382 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Shut your stupid trap!
-See ya, Pas.

00:11:21.516 --> 00:11:23.552 position:24% line:83% align:start
Be sure to have fun
on your trip, okay?

00:11:23.684 --> 00:11:24.985 position:44% line:89% align:start
Sure!

00:11:25.119 --> 00:11:26.387 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'll eat lots and lots
of delicious things

00:11:26.521 --> 00:11:27.755 position:30% line:89% align:start
while I'm gone!

00:11:27.888 --> 00:11:29.423 position:13% line:83% align:start
Oh! Everything's about food
with him.

00:11:29.558 --> 00:11:31.458 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, that's our Pas, after all!

00:11:31.892 --> 00:11:33.060 position:13% line:89% align:start
You're in charge, Feuille.

00:11:33.194 --> 00:11:34.094 position:38% line:89% align:start
Yes, sir!

00:11:34.228 --> 00:11:37.198 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:11:37.331 --> 00:11:42.369 position:27% line:89% align:start
[wind whooshing]

00:11:55.816 --> 00:11:57.284 position:27% line:89% align:start
[children oohing]

00:11:58.587 --> 00:12:01.355 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:12:14.435 --> 00:12:15.903 position:27% line:89% align:start
That was awesome!

00:12:16.036 --> 00:12:19.306 position:16% line:83% align:start
Lord Casserole, his magic
is really something else.

00:12:20.407 --> 00:12:22.510 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[AGNES] Josie.
-[JOSEPHINE] Yes, Mother.

00:12:23.511 --> 00:12:24.945 position:24% line:83% align:start
[AGNES, JOSEPHINE]
We'll never forget

00:12:25.079 --> 00:12:27.047 position:24% line:83% align:start
that Pas looks best
in a pretty dress!

00:12:28.249 --> 00:12:30.751 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[crowed chatter]
-[Pas gasps]

00:12:30.884 --> 00:12:32.886 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
The capital doesn't disappoint!

00:12:33.020 --> 00:12:34.888 position:19% line:83% align:start
This is the most people
I've seen in one place

00:12:35.022 --> 00:12:36.890 position:10% line:89% align:start
ever since my reincarnation!

00:12:37.024 --> 00:12:38.526 position:33% line:89% align:start
Look, Father!

00:12:38.660 --> 00:12:40.995 position:10% line:83% align:start
There are so many things here
I've never seen before!

00:12:41.128 --> 00:12:43.264 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Is that brown sugar?

00:12:43.397 --> 00:12:44.365 position:35% line:89% align:start
And fruit?

00:12:44.832 --> 00:12:48.102 position:24% line:83% align:start
The Fief of Morteln
is so bereft of sweet things,

00:12:48.235 --> 00:12:50.104 position:30% line:83% align:start
I've never seen
this stuff there!

00:12:50.237 --> 00:12:51.772 position:19% line:89% align:start
With these ingredients:

00:12:51.905 --> 00:12:56.043 position:5% line:83% align:start
brown sugar cookies, pound cake,
chocolate gÃ¢teau, flan!

00:12:56.176 --> 00:12:58.647 position:41% line:83% align:start
[sighs]
The possibilities are endless.

00:12:58.779 --> 00:12:59.880 position:27% line:89% align:start
I'm raring to go!

00:13:00.014 --> 00:13:01.282 position:13% line:89% align:start
Listen, if you can make it

00:13:01.415 --> 00:13:03.450 position:41% line:83% align:start
through
the Sanctification Ceremony,

00:13:03.585 --> 00:13:04.719 position:30% line:89% align:start
as your reward,

00:13:04.852 --> 00:13:05.953 position:30% line:83% align:start
I will buy you
whatever you like.

00:13:06.086 --> 00:13:07.288 position:33% line:89% align:start
You mean it?

00:13:07.421 --> 00:13:08.455 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hooray!

00:13:08.590 --> 00:13:10.592 position:47% line:83% align:start
Oh,
but how can I narrow it down?

00:13:10.725 --> 00:13:12.426 position:5% line:89% align:start
I wonder what I should ask for.

00:13:12.560 --> 00:13:13.662 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:13:13.794 --> 00:13:16.096 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Are those... apples?

00:13:16.230 --> 00:13:17.998 position:19% line:83% align:start
And they look so juicy
and delicious! [gasps]

00:13:18.132 --> 00:13:20.401 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm so glad to know
they exist in this world, too!

00:13:20.535 --> 00:13:23.170 position:10% line:83% align:start
-I believe those are bonkas.
-Bonkas?

00:13:23.304 --> 00:13:25.873 position:24% line:83% align:start
They're cultivated
up in the northern lands.

00:13:26.006 --> 00:13:28.409 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's rare to see them
even in the market.

00:13:28.543 --> 00:13:30.144 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
I have scarcely tasted them,

00:13:30.277 --> 00:13:33.080 position:24% line:83% align:start
though I recall it
being on the sour side.

00:13:33.581 --> 00:13:34.982 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Sour, huh?

00:13:35.115 --> 00:13:38.385 position:5% line:83% align:start
There are all kinds of neat ways
to use sour apples!

00:13:38.520 --> 00:13:39.754 position:33% line:89% align:start
Say, Father,

00:13:39.887 --> 00:13:41.656 position:16% line:83% align:start
let's try growing bonkas
when we get back!

00:13:41.790 --> 00:13:45.092 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Growing them?
-Yes, let's bring some with us!

00:13:45.560 --> 00:13:46.427 position:41% line:89% align:start
Really?

00:13:47.194 --> 00:13:48.530 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Such a keen interest

00:13:48.663 --> 00:13:50.097 position:7% line:89% align:start
in the goods of foreign lands.

00:13:50.230 --> 00:13:53.133 position:10% line:83% align:start
He's developing the instincts
of a true suzerain!

00:13:53.267 --> 00:13:55.002 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
If I got five of them,

00:13:55.135 --> 00:13:57.338 position:33% line:83% align:start
I could make
all kinds of things.

00:14:01.810 --> 00:14:03.844 position:13% line:89% align:start
I'd love to try them glacÃ©,

00:14:03.977 --> 00:14:07.081 position:38% line:83% align:start
however,
sugar itself is such a luxury!

00:14:07.214 --> 00:14:09.049 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm sure it's too much to ask.

00:14:09.450 --> 00:14:12.353 position:13% line:83% align:start
Uh, What if we raised bees
in our fief?

00:14:12.486 --> 00:14:14.888 position:24% line:83% align:start
I could candy them
in honey instead!

00:14:15.724 --> 00:14:17.726 position:24% line:89% align:start
Tart, baked apples,

00:14:17.858 --> 00:14:20.795 position:5% line:89% align:start
and the old classic, apple pie!

00:14:21.295 --> 00:14:22.429 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
With talent like his,

00:14:22.564 --> 00:14:24.532 position:19% line:83% align:start
the future of the fief
will be...

00:14:25.032 --> 00:14:26.433 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
If I can cultivate apples,

00:14:26.568 --> 00:14:29.269 position:19% line:83% align:start
the future of the fief
will be...

00:14:30.037 --> 00:14:32.139 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
A rich and mighty land!

00:14:32.272 --> 00:14:35.042 position:33% line:83% align:start
[PAS] A land
of all-you-can-eat sweets!

00:14:36.110 --> 00:14:37.211 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
We're here.

00:14:37.612 --> 00:14:39.380 position:30% line:89% align:start
[door creaking]

00:14:40.347 --> 00:14:43.016 position:27% line:83% align:start
Well, if it isn't
the Lord of Morteln himself.

00:14:43.150 --> 00:14:44.318 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Ah!
-[PRIEST] Thank you for coming

00:14:44.451 --> 00:14:46.120 position:30% line:83% align:start
-all this way.
-[PAS] Human panda?

00:14:46.253 --> 00:14:48.188 position:24% line:83% align:start
Greetings, Father.
It's an honor to see you again.

00:14:48.322 --> 00:14:49.624 position:7% line:89% align:start
I believe the last time we met

00:14:49.758 --> 00:14:52.192 position:19% line:83% align:start
was at your daughter's
Sanctification Ceremony.

00:14:52.326 --> 00:14:54.461 position:13% line:83% align:start
You did me a great service
that day.

00:14:54.596 --> 00:14:57.097 position:13% line:83% align:start
I've heard wonderful tales
about you, milord.

00:14:57.231 --> 00:14:59.466 position:7% line:83% align:start
For instance, that you somehow
protected your people

00:14:59.601 --> 00:15:01.870 position:10% line:83% align:start
when last year's bitter frost
threatened the worst.

00:15:02.002 --> 00:15:03.470 position:16% line:89% align:start
Truly, it was achievable

00:15:03.605 --> 00:15:05.973 position:13% line:83% align:start
only through the good grace
of God and the Spirits,

00:15:06.106 --> 00:15:08.610 position:24% line:83% align:start
and with some help
from my son's wisdom.

00:15:08.743 --> 00:15:11.111 position:19% line:83% align:start
Ah, and you've brought
that very son with you.

00:15:11.245 --> 00:15:12.847 position:10% line:89% align:start
This will come as a surprise,

00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:15.583 position:7% line:83% align:start
but I intend for him to undergo
his Sanctification Ceremony

00:15:15.717 --> 00:15:17.284 position:38% line:89% align:start
at once.

00:15:17.418 --> 00:15:20.220 position:13% line:83% align:start
My word, you can't possibly
be serious about this, milord!

00:15:20.354 --> 00:15:24.559 position:5% line:83% align:start
Yet I am. A True Sanctification,
nothing less will do.

00:15:24.692 --> 00:15:25.660 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:15:27.762 --> 00:15:28.663 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Pas grunts]

00:15:29.731 --> 00:15:31.031 position:33% line:89% align:start
Hey, Feuille.

00:15:31.165 --> 00:15:32.867 position:7% line:83% align:start
So isn't "True Sanctification"
the ceremony

00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:34.435 position:21% line:89% align:start
where you get magic?

00:15:34.569 --> 00:15:35.169 position:38% line:89% align:start
Correct,

00:15:35.302 --> 00:15:36.538 position:24% line:89% align:start
and that's the one

00:15:36.671 --> 00:15:38.105 position:24% line:83% align:start
your kid brother's
going to undertake.

00:15:38.238 --> 00:15:39.440 position:19% line:89% align:start
When I did my Ceremony,

00:15:39.574 --> 00:15:41.241 position:38% line:83% align:start
they said
I had little magic power.

00:15:41.375 --> 00:15:43.076 position:19% line:83% align:start
Without any true magic
to my name,

00:15:43.210 --> 00:15:44.378 position:27% line:83% align:start
they didn't feel
it was necessary

00:15:44.512 --> 00:15:46.246 position:5% line:89% align:start
to put me through that hardship.

00:15:46.380 --> 00:15:47.682 position:13% line:89% align:start
I hope he'll be all right.

00:15:47.816 --> 00:15:48.949 position:35% line:89% align:start
Sweet Pas.

00:15:49.082 --> 00:15:50.417 position:19% line:83% align:start
I think he'll be fine,
Josephine.

00:15:50.552 --> 00:15:51.586 position:35% line:89% align:start
Worry not.

00:15:51.719 --> 00:15:52.821 position:35% line:83% align:start
[JOSEPHINE]
What's that ceremony like?

00:15:52.953 --> 00:15:55.690 position:13% line:89% align:start
Hm. How can I describe it?

00:15:56.223 --> 00:15:58.192 position:16% line:83% align:start
They measure the amount
of magic power you have,

00:15:58.325 --> 00:16:00.027 position:13% line:89% align:start
and that's just the start.

00:16:00.562 --> 00:16:05.567 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:16:09.002 --> 00:16:10.003 position:38% line:83% align:start
[PRIEST]
Now, child.

00:16:10.137 --> 00:16:11.639 position:33% line:89% align:start
Imbibe this.

00:16:14.542 --> 00:16:16.243 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
[grunts] Too bitter!

00:16:16.376 --> 00:16:17.745 position:10% line:89% align:start
What the hell is this stuff?

00:16:17.879 --> 00:16:19.146 position:38% line:83% align:start
[PRIEST]
Hm.

00:16:19.279 --> 00:16:20.113 position:19% line:83% align:start
-[JOSEPHINE] What then?
-[Pas grunting]

00:16:20.247 --> 00:16:21.482 position:19% line:89% align:start
You don't do anything.

00:16:21.616 --> 00:16:24.017 position:41% line:83% align:start
[gasps]
And what do you mean by that?

00:16:24.586 --> 00:16:25.720 position:33% line:89% align:start
[door creaks]

00:16:25.854 --> 00:16:28.422 position:7% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE] You're left all alone
in the dark.

00:16:28.790 --> 00:16:31.058 position:19% line:89% align:start
Unable to see or hear.

00:16:31.191 --> 00:16:34.495 position:21% line:89% align:start
For hours and hours.

00:16:35.630 --> 00:16:36.831 position:41% line:89% align:start
Magic.

00:16:36.965 --> 00:16:40.033 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's a grand power
hidden within certain people.

00:16:40.568 --> 00:16:43.003 position:21% line:83% align:start
This is the only way
to draw it out.

00:16:43.538 --> 00:16:47.742 position:10% line:83% align:start
To face and overcome hardship
all by yourself.

00:16:56.818 --> 00:16:58.085 position:35% line:89% align:start
[sparkling]

00:16:58.218 --> 00:16:59.621 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
It's been a day and a half.

00:17:00.354 --> 00:17:02.957 position:21% line:83% align:start
Surely this is longer
than necessary.

00:17:03.090 --> 00:17:04.993 position:35% line:83% align:start
No, I fear
we cannot release your son

00:17:05.125 --> 00:17:08.295 position:13% line:83% align:start
until the radiance subsides
whenever that may come to pass.

00:17:08.428 --> 00:17:10.430 position:38% line:83% align:start
[PRIEST]
That said, it's most impressive

00:17:10.565 --> 00:17:12.534 position:30% line:83% align:start
that the moment
has not yet come.

00:17:12.934 --> 00:17:14.134 position:16% line:89% align:start
The boy must be harboring

00:17:14.268 --> 00:17:17.104 position:10% line:83% align:start
a magnificent level of power
within.

00:17:17.572 --> 00:17:18.673 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Understood.

00:17:19.039 --> 00:17:20.474 position:5% line:89% align:start
Do you think he'll be all right?

00:17:20.608 --> 00:17:22.442 position:19% line:83% align:start
There is no real cause
for concern,

00:17:22.577 --> 00:17:24.411 position:24% line:83% align:start
though so much time
in darkness and silence

00:17:24.546 --> 00:17:26.581 position:19% line:89% align:start
would surely be trying.

00:17:26.714 --> 00:17:27.615 position:41% line:89% align:start
My boy.

00:17:29.182 --> 00:17:30.518 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
What will I do?

00:17:30.652 --> 00:17:32.954 position:24% line:83% align:start
What should I make
with those bonkas?

00:17:33.621 --> 00:17:36.056 position:5% line:89% align:start
My imagination is running wild!

00:17:36.189 --> 00:17:39.359 position:16% line:83% align:start
Someday, I'll find a way
to get sugar, too!

00:17:39.493 --> 00:17:41.428 position:16% line:89% align:start
Then the sky's the limit!

00:17:41.563 --> 00:17:44.832 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm filled with glee
just thinking about it.

00:17:44.966 --> 00:17:46.601 position:24% line:89% align:start
My dream is alive,

00:17:46.734 --> 00:17:49.202 position:27% line:83% align:start
to fill the land
with perfect sweets!

00:17:49.336 --> 00:17:51.606 position:30% line:83% align:start
To bring smiles
to everyone's faces!

00:17:51.739 --> 00:17:53.975 position:19% line:83% align:start
To make the best treats
in the world!

00:17:54.107 --> 00:17:57.110 position:19% line:83% align:start
That must be the reason
I was reincarnated in this place

